SAF-Holland Sees Sales Rise of Up to 25%, Borghardt Tells WiWo

-- B y   O l i v e r   S u e s s
-- 
2011-05-28T10:27:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-28/saf-holland-sees-sales-rise-of-up-to-25-borghardt-tells-wiwo.html
SAF-Holland SA (SFQ) , a German supplier of
parts for truck trailers, expects a sales increase of up to 25
percent this year,  WirtschaftsWoche  reported, citing an
interview with Detlef Borghardt, who will become chief executive
officer from July 1.  SAF, based in Bessenbach,  Germany , aims to achieve sales of
1 billion euros ($1.4 billion) over the next three to five
years, the magazine cited Borghardt as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Oliver Suess in Munich at 
